1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:04,800
Science has a clearer story about phytoplankton blooms than social media does.

2
00:00:04,800 --> 00:00:10,800
These tiny organisms are the backbone of marine ecosystems, producing half of the world's oxygen.

3
00:00:10,800 --> 00:00:13,600
But what happens when they bloom excessively?

4
00:00:13,600 --> 00:00:15,200
It's a double-edged sword.

5
00:00:15,200 --> 00:00:21,200
While blooms can boost fish populations, they can also deplete oxygen, leading to dead zones.

6
00:00:21,200 --> 00:00:26,400
Understanding these blooms helps us manage our oceans better and protect marine life.

7
00:00:26,400 --> 00:00:28,400
Curious about more ocean mysteries?

8
00:00:28,400 --> 00:00:30,000
Hit that follow button!
